# Mks-Robin Lite
Mks-Robin Lite Firmware version description

Mks-Robin Lite V0.01

     Initial version
     
1.Firmware options

Mks-Robin Lite: Robin_Lite.bin

2.Mks-Robin Lite V0.04 function description

  2.1.Control chip: 32-bit ARM
  2.2.External WIFI module for cloud printing
  2.3.Multi-language:Chinese;English
  2.4.Continue printing after power off
  2.5.Dislay:LCD

<b>The build may fail with the following error.</b>
<h3 style="color:Tomato;">In file included from .piolibdeps/mks_robin_lite/TMCStepper_ID5513/src/source/CHOPCONF.cpp:1:0:
.piolibdeps/mks_robin_lite/TMCStepper_ID5513/src/TMCStepper.h:18:11: fatal error: SoftwareSerial.h: No such file or directory</h3>
<b> To fix the complier error:
Open the the file ../MKS-Robin/MKS Robin Lite/firmware/Marlin2.0-MKS-Robin_lite/.piolibdeps/mks_robin_lite/TMCStepper_ID5513/src/TMCStepper.h
Find the line with #define SW_CAPABLE_PLATFORM defined.
Comment the | defined(ARDUINO_ARCH_STM32F1) as shown below.
<h3 style="color:Tomato;">#define SW_CAPABLE_PLATFORM defined(__AVR__) || defined(TARGET_LPC1768) || defined(ARDUINO_ARCH_ESP32) //|| defined(ARDUINO_ARCH_STM32F1) </h3>
<b> Details of the issue canbe found in Marlin Firmware's GitHub. However the MKS RObin Lite repo does not have the fix yet.</b>
   
